We intend to keep compatible with 1.4.2 for now -- that commit slipped
in inadvertently, and will be fixed.

In advance of some future official release, we&#39;ll announce it as the
last release with official support for 1.4.2, and after that start
using 1.5 features purposefully.

What would people think of the next official release, 1.6 likely
some time in November, being the last 1.4.2-compatible release?
Would it be better to maintain 1.4.2-compatibility for the next
2 or more releases?

Are there any platforms people are using for which 1.5.0 is
unavailable or flaky?

- Gordon @ IA

